# CVE-2026-42559 — rmcp 0.16.0 Streamable HTTP transport DNS-rebinding.
# MITIGATED at the application layer: guard_middleware validates the Origin
# header and rejects cross-origin browser requests (see
# crates/server/src/main.rs `HttpGuard::origin_allowed` + the
# `cross_origin_request_is_rejected` test). A DNS-rebinding page cannot reach
# /mcp because its browser Origin is neither loopback nor allow-listed.
# TRACKED: remove this ignore once the crate is upgraded to rmcp >= 1.4.0
# (a major-version migration handled as its own task).
CVE-2026-42559
